{"title_page": "Syed Akbar Pasha Tirmizi", "text_new": "{{Infobox religious biography\n| name = Syed Akbar Pasha Tirmizi\n| image = \n| birth_date         = June 6, 1944 (age 75)\n| birth_place     = [[British India]] [[Hoshiapur]]\n| children           =  5 \n| religion           = [[Islam]]\n| occupation         = [[Translator]], [[Advocate]]\n| parents         = Syed Ishrat Ali Shah (father)\n| works = Unity of Mankind, Dawn Of Rationality\n| influences = [[Josh Malihabadi]], [[Ali Shariati]]\n}}\n\n{{Shia Islam}}\n\n'''Syed Akbar Pasha Tirmizi''' ({{lang-ur|{{Nastaliq|\u0633\u06cc\u062f \u0627\u06a9\u0628\u0631 \u067e\u0627\u0634\u0627 \u062a\u0631\u0645\u0630\u06cc}}}}) is a Pakistani translator for the English language and is an [[Advocate]] born in British India in 1944. He is a [[sayyid]] and descendant of [[Ali al-Hadi]]. He grew up in early [[Pakistan]] and studied to become a lawyer/advocate once he had his LL.B, he went on to earn a M.A.<ref>https://www.al-islam.org/help/translations/view.asp?langfr=All&langto=English&nature=Book&status=Published</ref>\n\n==Works==\n[[File:Unity Mankind.jpg|thumb|One of the books of Syed: Translation of Josh Malihibadis poem in the English Language]]\nHe translated poems of [[Josh Malihabadi]] from [[urdu]] to [[English language|English]]. Syed Akbar Pasha has already translated the elegies of [[Josh Malihabadi]] from urdu into English in the form of verses under title *Unity of mankind*, besides this, he has translated in urdu the Dr [[Ali Shariati]]'s books *Hajj*. In the book ''Unity of Mankind'', Its translators are Syed Akbar Pasha Tirmizi M.A.,LL.B and advocate; and Syed sibt-e- Ali Tirmizi ,a student of English literature& Masooma Fatima M.a .English literature who are his son and daughter respectively.<ref>Unity of Mankind, pg 185, 25</ref> Syed Akbar Pasha Tirmizi has also translated in the form of english verses the encomium of Josh Malihabadi *Taloo-e-Fikr*<ref>https://urdushahkar.org/00-tuloo-e-fikr-josh-malihabadi-00-overview/</ref><ref>https://www.rekhta.org/ebooks/tulu-e-fikr-josh-malihabadi-ebooks</ref> under the title *Dawn of Rationality* and has also to his credit the translation of Dr [[Ali Shariati]]'s  book *yes brother that is the way it was* into urdu. He studies law and gives his salutations to the [[Twelve Imams]].<ref>Comments on the 12 imams in the book ''unity of mankind''</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:1944 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Pakistani translators]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox religious biography\n| name = Syed Akbar Pasha Tirmizi\n| image = \n| birth_date         = June 6, 1944 (age 75)\n| birth_place     = [[British India]] [[Hoshiapur]]\n| children           =  5 \n| religion           = [[Islam]]\n| occupation         = [[Translator]], [[Advocate]]\n| parents         = Syed Ishrat Ali Shah (father)\n| works = Unity of Mankind, Dawn Of Rationality\n| influences = [[Josh Malihabadi]], [[Ali Shariati]]\n}}\n\n{{Shia Islam}}\n\n'''Syed Akbar Pasha Tirmizi''' ({{lang-ur|{{Nastaliq|\u0633\u06cc\u062f \u0627\u06a9\u0628\u0631 \u067e\u0627\u0634\u0627 \u062a\u0631\u0645\u0630\u06cc}}}}) is a Pakistani translator for the English language and is a [[Advocate]] born in British India in 1944. He is a [[sayyid]] and descendant of [[Ali al-Hadi]]. He grew up in early [[Pakistan]] and studied to become a lawyer/advocate once he had his LL.B, he went on to earn a M.A. <ref>https://www.al-islam.org/help/translations/view.asp?langfr=All&langto=English&nature=Book&status=Published</ref>\n\n==Works==\n[[File:Unity Mankind.jpg|thumb|One of the books of Syed: Translation of Josh Malihibadis peom in the English Language]]\nHe translated poems of [[Josh Malihabadi]] from [[urdu]] to [[English language|English]]. Syed Akbar Pasha has already translated the elegies of [[Josh Malihabadi]] from urdu into English in the form of verses under title *Unity of mankind*, besides this, he has translated in urdu the Dr [[Ali Shariati]]'s books *Hajj*. In the book ''Unity of Mankind'', Its translators are Syed Akbar Pasha Tirmizi M.A.,LL.B and advocate; and Syed sibt-e- Ali Tirmizi ,a student of English literature& Masooma Fatima M.a .English literature who are his son and daughter respectively.<ref>Unity of Mankind, pg 185, 25</ref> Syed Akbar Pasha Tirmizi has also translated in the form of english verses the encomium of Josh Malihabadi *Taloo-e-Fikr*<ref>https://urdushahkar.org/00-tuloo-e-fikr-josh-malihabadi-00-overview/</ref><ref>https://www.rekhta.org/ebooks/tulu-e-fikr-josh-malihabadi-ebooks</ref> under the title *Dawn of Rationality* and has also to his credit the translation of Dr [[Ali Shariati]]'s  book *yes brother that is the way it was* into urdu. He studies law and gives his salutations to the [[Twelve Imams]]. <ref>Comments on the 12 imams in the book ''unity of mankind''</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:1944 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Pakistani translators]]\n", "name_user": "John of Reading", "label": "safe", "comment": "Typo/generalfixes, replaced: aAdvocate\u2192 anAdvocate, peom \u2192 poem", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Syed_Akbar_Pasha_Tirmizi"}
